<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="264" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3094: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the Commission of Neutrals</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Secretary General of the League of Nations</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Drummond</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-12">May 12, 1933</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Commission of Neutrals acknowledges with thanks the receipt of your
                            radio 11th instant. The Commission, as always, is most desirous
                            cooperate with Council of League with view restoration and maintenance
                            peace.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>